    {"type":"text","id":"comb_sub","x":455,"y":64,"width":435,"height":14,"text":"nom (Rust), Parsec (Haskell), pyparsing (Python) — funciones que se componen","originalText":"nom (Rust), Parsec (Haskell), pyparsing (Python) — funciones que se componen","fontSize":11,"fontFamily":3,"textAlign":"center","verticalAlign":"top","strokeColor":"#92400e","backgroundColor":"transparent","fillStyle":"solid","strokeWidth":1,"strokeStyle":"solid","roughness":0,"opacity":100,"angle":0,"seed":95,"version":1,"versionNonce":96,"isDeleted":false,"groupIds":[],"boundElements":null,"link":null,"locked":false,"containerId":null,"lineHeight":1.25},

    {"type":"text","id":"comb_code","x":463,"y":84,"width":419,"height":60,"text":"// Una función = un parser\nfn number(input) → parse i64 from digits\nfn factor(input) → alt( delimited('(', expr, ')'), number )\nfn expr(input)   → separated_list('+', term) // compose!","originalText":"// Una función = un parser\nfn number(input) → parse i64 from digits\nfn factor(input) → alt( delimited('(', expr, ')'), number )\nfn expr(input)   → separated_list('+', term) // compose!","fontSize":11,"fontFamily":3,"textAlign":"left","verticalAlign":"top","strokeColor":"#92400e","backgroundColor":"transparent","fillStyle":"solid","strokeWidth":1,"strokeStyle":"solid","roughness":0,"opacity":100,"angle":0,"seed":97,"version":1,"versionNonce":98,"isDeleted":false,"groupIds":[],"boundElements":null,"link":null,"locked":false,"containerId":null,"lineHeight":1.4},
    {"type":"text","id":"comb_pros","x":463,"y":150,"width":419,"height":78,"text":"✓ Parsers son funciones normales → fácil de testear unitariamente\n✓ Composición: combinar parsers pequeños en grandes\n✓ No hay paso de generación — un solo pipeline de build\n✓ Mensajes de error directamente en tu lenguaje\n✗ Overhead si combinaciones son muy numerosas\n✗ Puede ser más lento que tablas LR para gramáticas grandes\n✗ Recursión mutua requiere cuidado (lazy evaluation)","originalText":"✓ Parsers son funciones normales → fácil de testear unitariamente\n✓ Composición: combinar parsers pequeños en grandes\n✓ No hay paso de generación — un solo pipeline de build\n✓ Mensajes de error directamente en tu lenguaje\n✗ Overhead si combinaciones son muy numerosas\n✗ Puede ser más lento que tablas LR para gramáticas grandes\n✗ Recursión mutua requiere cuidado (lazy evaluation)","fontSize":11,"fontFamily":3,"textAlign":"left","verticalAlign":"top","strokeColor":"#92400e","backgroundColor":"transparent","fillStyle":"solid","strokeWidth":1,"strokeStyle":"solid","roughness":0,"opacity":100,"angle":0,"seed":99,"version":1,"versionNonce":100,"isDeleted":false,"groupIds":[],"boundElements":null,"link":null,"locked":false,"containerId":null,"lineHeight":1.4},

